title.narrative: PARTICIPATION

description.narrative: Adolescent girls and boys have opportunities to participate in decision-making as well as contribute to social cohesion in their communities and sustainable development at national level, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Operations Support To Programme Delivery. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Adolescents, including the most marginalized , are recognized as equal members of society and empowered to participate meaningfully in all aspects of life

description.narrative: Adolescent participation platform expanded within the Youth Friendly Local Governance in eight districts, enabled the local governments to conduct situation analyses around children and youth issues. As a result, 51 issues raised by the adolescent girls and boys during consultations with the local government were included into the District Development plans of eight districts and implemented by adolescents jointly with the local governments. The initiative engaged 32,594 (15,195 females) young people in communities&39; development. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
